        <h1>LeetCode 3867: Sum of GCD of Formed Pairs (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array nums. For each index i, compute the GCD of the maximum element in
                nums[0..i] and nums[i]. Then sort the resulting values array and pair elements from both ends, summing
                the GCD of each pair. Return the total sum.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [4,2,6,3]<br>
                Output: some value<br>
                Explanation: Compute GCD of running max and each element: GCD(4,4)=4, GCD(4,2)=2, GCD(6,6)=6,
                GCD(6,3)=3. Sort: [2,3,4,6]. Pair (2,6) and (3,4): GCD(2,6)+GCD(3,4) = 2+1 = 3.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    long long gcdSum(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        vector&lt;int&gt; values(nums.size());
        long long result = 0;
        int largest = 0;
        for (int idx = 0; idx &lt; nums.size(); idx++) {
            largest = max(largest, nums[idx]);
            values[idx] = gcd(largest, nums[idx]);
        }
        sort(values.begin(), values.end());
        int left = 0;
        int right = values.size() - 1;
        // Pair values from both ends.
        while (left &lt; right) {
            result += gcd(values[left], values[right]);
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        return result;
    }
};</code></pre>
